    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Trademarked term for a particular type of digital duplicating machine made by the Riso company that employs soy-based inks. Copies are created by scanning an image, burning it to a laser-etched stencil that is wrapped around a drum containing ink that rolls over continuously fed paper to create copies very rapidly.</Note_Text>
